def: A person born of relations between whom marriage was forbiddenby the Mosaic law; a bastard. Deut. xxiii. 2 (Douay version).
Equal in measure but not admitting of superposition; -- appliedto magnitudes; as, a square may be equivalent to a triangle.
To jest; to play tricks; to jeer. [Obs.] Chaucer.
Having a clear physical or mental vision; having a clearunderstanding.
A margin; border; brink; edge. [Obs.]The beached margent of the sea. Shak.

Any one of several species of neuropterous insects of the genusChrysopa and allied genera. They have delicate, lacelike wings andbrilliant eyes. Their larv√¶ are useful in destroying aphids. Calledalso lace-winged fly, and goldeneyed fly.
One who adheres to, or is skilled in, the objective philosophy.Ed. Rev.
See Wondrous. [Obs.]They be wonders glad thereof. Sir T. More.
A gossat, or rockling; -- called also whistler, three-beardedrockling, sea loach, and sorghe.
Single-voiced; having but one part; as, a monophoniccomposition; -- opposed to Ant: polyphonic.
